import pandas as pd 
import numpy as np 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt 

df = pd.read_csv('fsp_case_31_BSD.csv', index_col = 0, header = [0,1])
df = df.replace(r'^\s+$', np.nan, regex=True)

df2 = df['ret'].copy() 
df.index = pd.to_datetime(df2.index) 
df2 = df2.iloc[:, -10:]

df_train = df2.iloc[:int(df2.shape[0]/2), :]
df_test = df2.iloc[int(df2.shape[0]/2):, :]

equally_weighted_portfolio_train = df_train.mean(1)
equally_weighted_portfolio_test = df_test.mean(1)

m_o = np.ones((df_train.shape[1],1))
C = df_train.cov() 
lamd = 1/(m_o.T.dot(np.linalg.inv(C).T).dot(m_o))
optimal_weights = lamd*(np.linalg.inv(C).dot(m_o))
optimal_weights = optimal_weights.reshape(-1,)

mvp_train = (df_train * optimal_weights).sum(1)

mvp_train.plot(color = 'blue')
plt.title('Optimally Weighted Portfolio Returns for Train Set', fontname="arial", fontsize=14, fontweight="bold")

In [16]:
df = pd.read_csv('fsp_case_31_BSD.csv', index_col=0,header=[0 ,1]) 
rs = df['ret'].copy().dropna(1) 
rs.index = pd.to_datetime(rs.index) 
rs = rs.iloc[:,-10:] 

ret_train = rs.iloc[:int(rs.shape[0]/2), :]
ret_test = rs.iloc[int(rs.shape[0]/2):, :]

def optimal_w (C):
    m_o = np.ones((ret_train.shape[1],1))
    Lambda = 1/(m_o.T.dot(np.linalg.inv(C).T).dot(m_o))
    optimal_weights_final = Lambda*(np.linalg.inv(C).dot(m_o))
    optimal_weights_final = optimal_weights_final.reshape(-1,)
    return optimal_weights_final

amvp = pd.Series() 
optimal_weights_finals = []
w = 22 

for t in ret_test.index: 
    
    ret_tmp = rs[:t].iloc[-w-1:-1] 
    cov_tmp = ret_tmp.cov() 
    optimal_weights_final = optimal_w(cov_tmp) 
    optimal_weights_finals.append(optimal_weights_final) 
    amvp[t] = sum(ret_test.loc[t]*optimal_weights_final) 
    
amvp.plot(color = 'blue')

plt.title('Adaptive Minimum-Variance Portfolio Returns for Test Set', fontname="arial", fontsize=14, fontweight="bold")

plt.xlabel('Date', fontname="arial", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Portfolio Returns', fontname="arial", fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(fontname="arial", fontsize=10)
plt.yticks(fontname="arial", fontsize=10)

plt.grid(which='major', linestyle='-', linewidth='0.5', color='#666666')
plt.minorticks_on()
plt.grid(b=True, which='minor', color='#999999', linestyle='-', alpha=0.2)

fig = plt.gcf()
fig.set_size_inches(6, 4)
